a.xlink:title: the full description of a font; the node name is the integer font id or "geda_pcb" for font 0 (for historical reasons); the name is used only to make each node unique, the ID is also a field below
unique font ID within the fontkit; fonts are referenced by ID
user specified, user readable font name
a collections of glyphs availbale in the font

Description of a glyph (symbol). Node name is a signel ASCII character or is of format &xx where xx is a hex digit of the ASCII code of the character. Characters that must use the hex version are: codes below 33 or over 126, &, #, {, }, /, :, ;, =, \, :
extra space always inserted after the current symbol, before the next character
objects that make up the symbol; IDs are per symbol local IDs counted from 0
round cap arc, simplified; contains a flat list of coords; each coord pair is an x;y corner of the outline of the polygon (odd indices are x coords, even indices are y coords)
radius (of the centerline of the arc)
width of the pen the arc is drawn with
